Lodash will respect undefined properties in find/findIndex if the object's level is only one:

``` javascript
_.find([{a:1}, {a:1, b:1}], {a:1, b:undefined})
//{ a: 1 }
_.findIndex([{a:1}, {a:1, b:1}], {a:1, b:undefined})
//0
```

However when giving a multi-level object to search for, it doesn't respect undefined properties in the search string:

``` javascript
_.find([{t:{a:1}}, {t:{a:1, b:1}}], {t:{a:1, b:undefined}})
//undefined
_.findIndex([{t:{a:1}}, {t:{a:1, b:1}}], {t:{a:1, b:undefined}})
//-1
```

